article.description: Chelsea Davis came off the bench to score a career-high 25 points and Alexa Deluzio added 20 points and eight rebounds as Florida State halted a two-game losing streak with a 94-74 win over Georgia State on Monday night.
article.headline: Chelsea Davis scores 25 off the bench to help Florida State end skid
article.linkText: FSU snaps 2-game skid by winning home debut
article.story:
TALLAHASSEE, Fla. --  Chelsea Davis came off the bench to score a career-high 25 points and Alexa Deluzio added 20 points and eight rebounds as Florida State (No. 19 ESPN/USA Today) halted a two-game losing streak with a 94-74 win over Georgia State on Monday night.

Chasity Clayton added 18 points and eight rebounds and Cierra Bravard had 11 points and nine rebounds for the Seminoles (3-2), who fell from the Top 25 on Monday afternoon after losses to Arkansas and Florida.

Kendra Long scored 18 points and Chan Harris fouled out with 12 points and seven rebounds for Georgia State (0-2), which shot 53.8 percent (7 of 13) form 3-point range.

Georgia State had 18 turnovers.

Deluzio made 10 of 12 free throws for Florida State, which made 33 of 43 (76.7 percent) from the line.

Florida State, which won its home opener for the 13th straight season, outrebounded Georgia State 48-34.
